<H3>Manage mp3 Play Lists (V2 Only)</H3>
<p>This feature only works if:
<OL>
<li><p>You have firmware version 2.
<li><p>You're using a miniSD card to store (and play) your mp3 files.
</OL>
<p>To use this feature, perform the following steps:
<OL>
<li><p>Make sure that the miniSD card is in the phone, and you can view and play your mp3 files off the card.
<li><p>Retrieve the list of mp3 files and play lists from your phone:
	<OL>
	<li><p>Menu <B>Data</B> -> <B>Get Phone Data</B>.
	<li><p>Check on <B>Play List</B>, and click on <B>OK</B>.
	</OL>
<li><p>In BitPim, click on the <B>Play List</B> tab, and edit (and save) your play lists.
<li><p>Write the play lists back to the phone:
	<OL>
	<li><p>Menu <B>Data</B> -> <B>Send Phone Data</B>.
	<li><p>Check on <B>Play List</B> and click on <B>OK</B>.
	</OL>
<li><p>Verify your new play list data on the phone.
</OL>
<p>Notes:
<UL>
<li><p>BitPim will not write empty play lists to the phone.
<li><p>BitPim will not write non-existent mp3 file(s) (as part of a play list) to the phone.
</UL>
